opened.title: unable to run defaultcharacter with ModelProviderName.LLAMACLOUD local
opened.body:
I'm trying to run the latest eliza with the defaultcharacter with the local Ollama.   starts up fine but as soon as I try to interact with it, it crashes saying it can't find the embeddingModel, but that's not the one that's configured as part of LLAMACLOUD

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1c9ea2f5-8de2-44a4-ac77-d9c99b6dc03d)

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/102774c1-c422-4c48-928f-e3f685d00d04)

this is the correct embedding and I have it installed:
![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2eeba077-2113-42f3-96f8-e39cf84a8bda)

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f564efdc-2023-4f32-b433-153b06c44268)

I even configured it in my .env file:
![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c3be0618-e46e-466c-893c-abab31f92493)

I'm starting at getting things running at the lowest level and then start adding clients one at a time.

It seems like there is something not right in DirectClient, but I can't put my finger on it.  For sure, there seems to be a few other provider related things hardcoded in there.

Let me know if I'm missing something.

comments.author: deepfates
comments.body: I think this is because of the mapping between model names in `modelProvider`. Solved this in my local character file by setting the lowercase version: `"modelProvider": "llama_cloud"`

opened.title: Linux dependency issues - discord voice client
opened.body:
**Describe the bug**

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->
when starting the discord client, the bot fails

**To Reproduce**
add discord client to character.json, pnpm start --character
<!-- Steps to reproduce the behavior. -->

**Expected behavior**
character initializes successfully
<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->

**Screenshots**

<!-- If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem. -->

**Additional context**
steps taken that resolve this issue:

```
sudo apt install node-gyp

pnpm add @octokit/core@3 -w

pnpm add @discordjs/opus@0.9.0 -w

pnpm add opusscript -w

pnpm add node-opus -w
```
this results in the bot being able to join discord voice and transcribe audio without crashing and function normally in chat responses, general 'does it run off a fresh pull' tracking issue
<!-- Add any other context about the problem here. -->

comments.author: sirkitree
comments.body:
Try the following:
1. downgrade to node v20 `nvm install 20 && nvm use 20`
1. remove node modules and lock file `rm -rf node_modules && rm pnpm-lock.yaml`
1. rerun install `pnpm i`
